#. @info:tooltip Help text for RGB spinbox.
#: colordialog.cpp:284
msgctxt "PerceptualColor::ColorDialogPrivate|"
msgid "<p>Red: 0вҒ вҖ“вҒ 255</p><p>Green: 0вҒ вҖ“вҒ 255</p><p>Blue: 0вҒ вҖ“вҒ 255</p>"
msgstr "<p>Roig: 0вҒ вҖ“вҒ 255</p><p>Verd: 0вҒ вҖ“вҒ 255</p><p>Blau: 0вҒ вҖ“вҒ 255</p>"

#. @info:tooltip Help text for hexadecimal code.
#: colordialog.cpp:291
msgctxt "PerceptualColor::ColorDialogPrivate|"
msgid ""
"<p>Hexadecimal color code, as used in HTML: #RRGGBB</p><p>RR: two-digit code "
"for red: 00вҒ вҖ“вҒ FF</p><p>GG: two-digit code for green: 00вҒ вҖ“вҒ FF</p><p>BB: two-digit "
"code for blue: 00вҒ вҖ“вҒ FF</p>"
msgstr ""
"<p>Codi de color hexadecimal, com s'utilitza en HTML: #RRGGBB</p><p>RR: codi "
"de dos dГӯgits per al roig: 00вҒ вҖ“вҒ FF</p><p>GG: codi de dos dГӯgits per al verd: "
"00вҒ вҖ“вҒ FF</p><p>BB: codi de dos dГӯgits per al blau: 00вҒ вҖ“вҒ FF</p>"

#. @info:tooltip Help text for HSL (hue, saturation, lightness). Saturation: 0 means something on the grey axis; 255 means something between the grey axis and the most colorful color. This is different from вҖңchromaвҖқ and should therefore get a different translation. Lightness: 0 means always black; 255 means always white. This is different from вҖңbrightnessвҖқ and should therefore get a different translation.
#: colordialog.cpp:304
msgctxt "PerceptualColor::ColorDialogPrivate|"
msgid ""
"<p>Hue: 0В°вҒ вҖ“вҒ 360В°</p><p>HSL-Saturation: 0%вҒ вҖ“вҒ 100%</p><p>Lightness: 0%вҒ вҖ“вҒ 100%</p>"
msgstr ""
"<p>To: 0В°вҒ вҖ“вҒ 360В°</p><p>SaturaciГі HSL: 0%вҒ вҖ“вҒ 100%</p><p>Claredat: 0%вҒ вҖ“вҒ 100%</p>"

#. @info:tooltip Help text for HWB (hue, whiteness, blackness). The idea behind is that the hue defines the pure (maximum colorful) color. Than, white color can be added, creating a вҖңtintвҖқ. Or black color can be added, creating a вҖңshadeвҖқ. Or both can be added, creating a вҖңtoneвҖң. See https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tint,_shade_and_tone for more information. 0% white + 0% black = pure color. 100% white + 0% black = white. 0% white + 100% black = black. 50% white + 50% black = gray. 50% white + 0% black = tint. 25% white + 25% black = tone. 0% white + 50% black = shade.
#: colordialog.cpp:318
msgctxt "PerceptualColor::ColorDialogPrivate|"
msgid "<p>Hue: 0В°вҒ вҖ“вҒ 360В°</p><p>Whiteness: 0%вҒ вҖ“вҒ 100%</p><p>Blackness: 0%вҒ вҖ“вҒ 100%</p>"
msgstr "<p>To: 0В°вҒ вҖ“вҒ 360В°</p><p>Blancor: 0%вҒ вҖ“вҒ 100%</p><p>Negror: 0%вҒ вҖ“вҒ 100%</p>"

#. @info:tooltip Help text for HSV/HSB. HSV (hue, saturation, value) and HSB (hue, saturation, brightness) are two different names for the very same color model. Saturation: 0 means something between black and white; 255 means something between black and the most colorful color. This is different from вҖңchromaвҖқ and should therefore get a different translation. Brightness/value: 0 means always black; 255 means something between white and the most colorful color. This is different from вҖңlightnessвҖқ and should therefore get a different translation.
#: colordialog.cpp:331
msgctxt "PerceptualColor::ColorDialogPrivate|"
msgid ""
"<p>Hue: 0В°вҒ вҖ“вҒ 360В°</p><p>HSV/HSB-Saturation: 0%вҒ вҖ“вҒ 100%</p><p>Brightness/Value: "
"0%вҒ вҖ“вҒ 100%</p>"
msgstr ""
"<p>To: 0В°вҒ вҖ“вҒ 360В°</p><p>SaturaciГі HSV/HSB: 0%вҒ вҖ“вҒ 100%</p><p>Brillantor/Valor: "
"0%вҒ вҖ“вҒ 100%</p>"

#. @label:slider Accessible name for lightness slider. This is different from вҖңbrightnessвҖқ/вҖңvalueвҖқ and should therefore get a different translation.
#: colordialog.cpp:342
msgctxt "PerceptualColor::ColorDialogPrivate|"
msgid "Lightness"
msgstr "Claredat"

#. @info:tooltip Help text for CIELCH. вҖңlightnessвҖқ is different from вҖңbrightnessвҖқ/вҖңvalueвҖқ and should therefore get a different translation.
#: colordialog.cpp:347
msgctxt "PerceptualColor::ColorDialogPrivate|"
msgid "<p>Lightness: 0%вҒ вҖ“вҒ 100%</p><p>Chroma: 0вҒ вҖ“вҒ %L1</p><p>Hue: 0В°вҒ вҖ“вҒ 360В°</p>"
msgstr "<p>Claredat: 0%вҒ вҖ“вҒ 100%</p><p>Croma: 0вҒ вҖ“вҒ %L1</p><p>To: 0В°вҒ вҖ“вҒ 360В°</p>"

#. @info:tooltip Help text for Oklch. вҖңlightnessвҖқ is different from вҖңbrightnessвҖқ/вҖңvalueвҖқ and should therefore get a different translation.
#: colordialog.cpp:356
msgctxt "PerceptualColor::ColorDialogPrivate|"
msgid ""
"<p>Lightness: %L1вҒ вҖ“вҒ %L2</p><p>Chroma: %L3вҒ вҖ“вҒ %L4</p><p>Hue: 0В°вҒ вҖ“вҒ 360В°</"
"p><p>Whitepoint: D65</p>"
msgstr ""
"<p>Claredat: %L1вҒ вҖ“вҒ %L2</p><p>Croma: %L3вҒ вҖ“вҒ %L4</p><p>To: 0В°вҒ вҖ“вҒ 360В°</p><p>Punt "
"blanc: D65</p>"

#. @label:slider An opacity of 0 means completely transparent. The higher the opacity value increases, the more opaque the colour becomes, until it finally becomes completely opaque at the highest possible opacity value.
#: colordialog.cpp:369
msgctxt "PerceptualColor::ColorDialogPrivate|"
msgid "Op&acity:"
msgstr "O&pacitat:"

